  "prompt_text": "Write a function to serialize and deserialize a binary tree. Explain your encoding scheme.",
  "response_text": "To serialize and deserialize a binary tree, we can use the Pre-order traversal method for serialization and the same or an in-order traversal method for deserialization. The pre-order traversal will give us a unique representation of the tree, which can be used to reconstruct the tree structure.\n\n### Serialization Function\nWe will encode each node's value followed by a special character (e.g., \"#\") if it is a leaf node or a space if it is not a leaf node (indicating further children). This way, we can uniquely represent the tree structure and values.\n\n```python\ndef serialize(root):\n    def preorder(node):\n        if not node:\n            return \"# \"\n        serialized = str(node.val) + \" \"\n        serialized += preorder(node.left)\n        serialized += preorder(node.right)\n        return serialized\n    \n    return preorder(root)\n```\n\n### Deserialization Function\nFor deserialization, we will split the serialized string into a list of nodes and recursively build the tree based on the pre-order traversal sequence.\n\n```python\ndef deserialize(data):\n    def build_tree(nodes):\n        val = next(nodes)\n        if val == \"#\":\n            return None\n        node = TreeNode(int(val))\n        node.left = build_tree(nodes)\n        node.right = build_tree(nodes)\n        return node\n    \n    nodes = iter(data.split())\n    return build_tree(nodes)\n```\n\n### Explanation\n- **Serialization**: We traverse the tree in a pre-order fashion (root, left, right). For each node, we append its value followed by a space. If the node is a leaf (no further children), we append `#` followed by a space. This ensures that the serialization is unique and allows for easy reconstruction during deserialization.\n- **Deserialization**: We split the serialized string into individual nodes using spaces as delimiters. Starting from the root, we use the pre-order sequence to reconstruct the tree by recursively building left and right subtrees.\n\n### Cognitive Engagement Ratings\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 7\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
